            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That's not a difference in Flask behavior, that's a different in Python behavior. hasattr on 2.x catches down all exceptions not just attribute errors. Use getattr instead as the docs suggest:\n\n``` python\nvalue = getattr(x, 'xyz', None)\nif value is not None:\n    ...\n```\n"
